2. cs.AR (Architecture) - The paper deals with allocating resources on computational hardware devices, which falls under the domain of computer architecture. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper describes algorithmic results for two crucial aspects of resource allocation, which is a core area of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with allocating resources on computational hardware devices, which can be relevant to distributed and parallel computing. 
5. cs.ET (Embedded Systems) - The paper deals with allocating resources on reconfigurable devices, which can be relevant to embedded systems.
